I've come here many times since they first opened. Way back, service and food was good. We used to consistently come here for a quick Chinese-Japanese meal and have absolutely no complaints. But, with time, the restaurant seemed to have gotten worse. After a year of not coming here, we decided to go for Mother's Day dinner. Their sushi chef were only focused on making sushi for take out, completely ignoring the dine-in guests orders. That was already frustrating. It took an hour for some simple sushi orders and other guests were waiting even longer.  And, to make matters worse, another table had asked how much longer the food is going to take because they've been waiting for a long time already. The boss gave them a nasty attitude and told him to leave, which they did. That's unacceptable. Not even an apology for the delay or an attempt to rectify the situation. The sushi, when it did come out, wasn't rolled well and crumbled upon being lifted. The wait staff did try their best despite the boss's complete disregard for his customers dining in, but there's only so much they can do when the ALL the sushi chefs are told to prioritize  the takeout over everyone in the restaurant.  Not coming here again -- the attitude is miserable and food quality has gone down.
